Feature: Update object scenarios

  @apiSmoke
  Scenario: Update a new object with existing json request
    Given I create a new object with random details
    And I send a POST request to object endpoint
    And the response status code is 200
    And the response should contain the following values:
      | name | Apple MacBook Pro 13 |
    When I get the object id
    And I update the object with existing data
    And I send a PUT request to update the object
    Then the response status code is 200
    And the response should contain the following values:
      | name | Apple MacBook Pro 12 |

  @apiSmoke
  Scenario: Update object name from Apple MacBook Pro 13 to 11
    Given I create a new object with random details
    And I send a POST request to object endpoint
    And the response status code is 200
    And the response should contain the following values:
      | name | Apple MacBook Pro 13 |
    When I get the object id
    And I update the object name with "Apple MacBook Pro 11"
    And I send a PUT request to update the object
    Then the response status code is 200
    And the response should contain the following values:
      | name | Apple MacBook Pro 11 |

  @apiSmoke
  Scenario: Attempt to update object with blank id
    Given I create a new object with random details
    And I send a PUT request to update the object
    Then the response status code is 404
    And the response should contain the following values:
      | error | The Object with id = null doesn't exist. Please provide an object id which exists or generate a new Object using POST request and capture the id of it to use it as part of PUT request after that. |

  @apiSmoke
  Scenario: Attempt to update an object that is unable
    When I send a PUT request to "/objects/7" with the updated object data
    Then the response status code is 405
    And the response should contain the following values:
      | error | 7 is a reserved id and the data object of it cannot be overridden. You can create a new object via POST request and use new generated by id from it to send a PUT request. |